  "original_title": "Sri Lanka NBRO issues landslide warning amid heavy rainfall expectation",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka NBRO issues landslide warning amid heavy rainfall expectation",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013\u00a0 Sri Lanka National Building Research Organization (NBRO) has issued landslide warnings to several areas in the country as higher rainfall exceeding 100 mm is expected during the day.",
        "Officials said heavy rainfall exceeding 75-100 mm can be expected in Sabaragamu, Western, Uva and North Western Provinces as well as in Kandy Nuwara Eliya, Galle and Matara districts.",
        "Accordingly, the NBRO has issued landslide warnings for the following areas.",
        "Kegalle District \u2013\u00a0Bulathkohupitiya, Dehiowita, Deraniyagala, Galigamuwa, Ruwanwella, Yatiyanthota and Kegalle Divisional Secretariat Division(s) (DSD) and surrounding areas.",
        "Nuwara Eliya District \u2013\u00a0Ambagamuwa Divisional Secretariat Division(s) (DSD) and surrounding areas.",
        "Ratnapura District \u2013\u00a0Ayagama, Eheliyagoda, Nivithigala, Ratnapura, Kuruwita and Elapatha Divisional Secretariat Division(s) (DSD) and surrounding areas."
      ],
